article.headline: Chattanooga over Furman 45-19
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- Jacob Huesman threw for two touchdowns and ran for two more as Chattanooga extended its undefeated conference record with a 45-19 win over Furman on Saturday. Huesman finished with 257 yards passing and 103 yards rushing to lead a Chattanooga offense that racked up 499 total yards. Furman had 325 yards overall. Keon Williams added to the numbers for the Mocs (9-3, 7-0 Southern Conference) with 97 yards rushing and two touchdowns. Tommy Hudson had 84 yards receiving. Huesman ran for two scores in the first half and threw for a third, a 17-yarder to Faysal Shafaat, in the final 32 seconds of the second quarter. Henrique Ribeiro added a 39-yard field goal and the Mocs were up 24-7 at the break. Williams ran for two scores in the third and Huesman hit Shafaat again in the fourth. P.J. Blazejowski threw for 127 yards for the Paladins (3-9, 2-5).
